reading 12.
the law is the foundation of liberty.
The mind, and spirit, and plan, and feeling, of the citizens is in the law.
Just as our body without mind, the state is not able to use its parts without the law.
the magistrates are the servents of the law , the interpreters of the law are the judges, and finally, we are the servants of the law therefore we can be free

reading 14.
if you, tullia, our light, if you are doing well, i and cicero are well. We came to athens, slowly and inconviently, because there were adverse winds. we walked down from the ship and acastus was present with letters at the time. I accepted your letters and letters from many friends.


